description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please indicate in your supporting information in which Team you would be interested.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen to recruit Community Mental Health Nurses to work in our lively and friendly Community Mental Health Recovery Services. We currently have vacancies in our Runnymede &amp; Spelthorne team based in Chertsey, Waverley team based in Godalming and Surrey Heath based in Frimley as follows:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Runnymede and Spelthorne CMHRS - 37.5 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Waverley CMHRS - 37.5 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Surrey Heath - 30 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be required to demonstrate a high level of commitment, motivation and knowledge working with people with severe and enduring mental health problems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be required to hold lead and professional responsibility for a number of service users. You will need to demonstrate excellent communication skills and be able to work collaboratively with a multidisciplinary team. You will be committed to the delivery of a high-quality service, working both independently and as part of a well-established, innovative and recovery-focused team in meeting the needs of service users and their carers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Within Surrey &amp; Borders Partnership NHS Foundation Trust we are keen on the development and training of staff, as such we would welcome both experienced applicants and applicants who wish to join us in one of our fantastic band 5 to 6 developmental roles. We would encourage applicants to contact the service for informal visits and discussions around the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates must have a full and valid driving licence and access to a vehicle for work purposes due to the community element of the role and the large geographical area that these teamscover.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
